<subSubSection id="C328651B852AED487CE91BE5FB963A73" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D3690852AED487CE91BE5FBA63BBB" blockId="7.[192,802,1667,1875]" lastBlockId="7.[830,1441,1545,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852AED487CE91BE5FEA03BBB" bold="true" box="[192,309,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Comments</emphasis>
: the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D13852AED487DED1BE2FD323BBB" authority="Simon, 1880" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[452,679,1668,1691]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Oiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852AED487DED1BE2FD9F3BBB" box="[452,522,1668,1691]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Oiclus</emphasis>
Simon, 1880
</taxonomicName>
, was considered to include a single polytypic species until very recently, when two additional new species were described (Teruel, 2008; Teruel &amp; Chazal, 2010). The specimens herein examined match the redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D13852AED487CE91A7BFE2A3A14" authority="purvesii" box="[192,447,1821,1844]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Oiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purvesii" subSpecies="purvesii">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852AED487CE91A7BFE2A3A14" box="[192,447,1821,1844]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Oiclus purvesii purvesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by Francke (1978), but we refrain from assigning the 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852AED487DF21A5AFDFA3A73" box="[475,623,1852,1875]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Sint Eustatius</collectingCountry>
specimens to a subspecies because the validity and scope of the two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D13852AED487FCB1B4EFBCA3B1F" baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[994,1119,1576,1599]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Oiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purvesii">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852AED487FCB1B4EFBCA3B1F" box="[994,1119,1576,1599]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">O. purvesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plus the supposedly hybrid population from 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852AED4878211B21FB103B7E" box="[1032,1157,1607,1630]" name="Saint Kitts and Nevis" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Saint Kitts</collectingCountry>
recognized by Francke (1978), are not satisfactory and need to be revised (Teruel &amp; Francke, 2006).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D3690852AED487F471BC5FB963A73" blockId="7.[830,1441,1545,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
This implies the first record of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D13852AED4879041BC5FAE73B9A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[1325,1394,1699,1722]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Oiclus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852AED4879041BC5FAE73B9A" box="[1325,1394,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Oiclus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D13852AED487FED1BA7FBC43BF8" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[964,1105,1729,1752]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scorpionidae</taxonomicName>
form 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852AED48788D1BA7FAD63BF8" box="[1188,1347,1729,1752]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Sint Eustatius</collectingCountry>
. It was expected, however, because populations had already been recorded from the neighboring islands of 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852AED4879171B99FAE73A36" box="[1342,1394,1791,1814]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Saba</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852AED487F691A7BFC273A14" box="[832,946,1821,1844]" name="Saint Kitts and Nevis" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Saint Kitts</collectingCountry>
(Francke, 1978; Sissom &amp; Fet, 2000; Teruel &amp; Francke, 2006).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
